1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,694
Welcome to the Parts Council Meditation.

2
00:00:02,694 --> 00:00:04,970
This is a more advanced practice.

3
00:00:04,970 --> 00:00:10,384
It is an invitation to listen to several
parts from Self-energy, without forcing

4
00:00:10,384 --> 00:00:12,029
agreement or resolution.

5
00:00:12,029 --> 00:00:18,193
If at any time this feels overwhelming,
you can pause, open your eyes, return to

6
00:00:18,193 --> 00:00:19,831
your breath, or stop.

7
00:00:19,831 --> 00:00:22,757
Begin by settling into your body.

8
00:00:22,757 --> 00:00:24,940
Let yourself arrive.

9
00:00:24,940 --> 00:00:26,844
Take a slow breath in.

10
00:00:35,844 --> 00:00:35,844
<break time="3s" />

11
00:00:35,844 --> 00:00:37,423
And let it out.

12
00:00:37,423 --> 00:00:39,373
Notice the room around you.

13
00:00:48,373 --> 00:00:48,373
<break time="3s" />

14
00:00:48,373 --> 00:00:51,856
Notice that you are here, in the present
moment.

15
00:00:51,856 --> 00:00:55,571
Now imagine a safe council space inside.

16
00:01:07,571 --> 00:01:07,571
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

17
00:01:07,571 --> 00:01:09,707
This might be a circle of chairs.

18
00:01:09,707 --> 00:01:10,543
A quiet room.

19
00:01:10,543 --> 00:01:11,843
A fire circle.

20
00:01:11,843 --> 00:01:13,515
A garden.

21
00:01:13,515 --> 00:01:15,001
A conference table.

22
00:01:15,001 --> 00:01:17,230
A place in nature.

23
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:21,131
Let it be a space where parts can gather
without being forced.

24
00:01:21,131 --> 00:01:25,311
Now invite Self-energy to be present at
the center of this space.

25
00:01:25,311 --> 00:01:26,426
Not as a boss.

26
00:01:26,426 --> 00:01:28,284
Not as a judge.

27
00:01:28,284 --> 00:01:31,860
But as a calm, curious, compassionate
presence.

28
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:33,021
Now ask:

29
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:45,021
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

30
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:48,086
Which parts want to be represented in
this council today?

31
00:02:00,086 --> 00:02:00,086
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

32
00:02:00,086 --> 00:02:02,222
Let parts appear one at a time.

33
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:03,615
There may be a manager.

34
00:02:03,615 --> 00:02:04,404
A critic.

35
00:02:04,404 --> 00:02:05,519
A protector.

36
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:06,912
A tired part.

37
00:02:06,912 --> 00:02:07,980
A young part.

38
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:09,327
A reactive part.

39
00:02:09,327 --> 00:02:11,231
A part that wants control.

40
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:13,135
A part that wants escape.

41
00:02:13,135 --> 00:02:15,411
Let whoever comes be noticed.

42
00:02:15,411 --> 00:02:17,965
Now choose one part to speak first.

43
00:02:17,965 --> 00:02:19,033
Ask:

44
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:21,912
What do you want the council to know?

45
00:02:33,912 --> 00:02:33,912
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

46
00:02:33,912 --> 00:02:34,934
Listen.

47
00:02:52,934 --> 00:02:52,934
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

48
00:02:52,934 --> 00:02:54,559
Now thank that part.

49
00:02:54,559 --> 00:02:56,231
Let it know it has been heard.

50
00:02:56,231 --> 00:02:58,739
Now invite another part to speak.

51
00:02:58,739 --> 00:02:59,621
Ask:

52
00:02:59,621 --> 00:03:02,686
What do you want the council to
understand?

53
00:03:14,686 --> 00:03:14,686
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

54
00:03:14,686 --> 00:03:15,661
Listen.

55
00:03:33,661 --> 00:03:33,661
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

56
00:03:33,661 --> 00:03:35,286
Thank that part.

57
00:03:35,286 --> 00:03:38,490
Now notice if any parts disagree with
each other.

58
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:43,459
Maybe one part wants closeness and
another wants distance.

59
00:03:43,459 --> 00:03:47,128
One wants rest and another wants
achievement.

60
00:03:47,128 --> 00:03:50,890
One wants expression and another wants
silence.

61
00:03:50,890 --> 00:03:53,258
This is polarization.

62
00:03:53,258 --> 00:03:55,998
It does not mean anything is wrong.

63
00:03:55,998 --> 00:04:00,224
It means parts are trying to protect in
different ways.

64
00:04:00,224 --> 00:04:02,407
Ask the council:

65
00:04:14,407 --> 00:04:14,407
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

66
00:04:14,407 --> 00:04:16,543
What are you each trying to protect?

67
00:04:28,543 --> 00:04:28,543
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

68
00:04:28,543 --> 00:04:29,704
Now ask:

69
00:04:41,704 --> 00:04:41,704
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

70
00:04:41,704 --> 00:04:45,280
What are you afraid would happen if you
stopped doing your job?

71
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:57,280
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

72
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,952
Listen without rushing.

73
00:04:58,952 --> 00:05:03,039
Now invite Self-energy to speak, if it
feels available.

74
00:05:03,039 --> 00:05:04,664
Not to command the parts.

75
00:05:04,664 --> 00:05:06,661
Not to fix them.

76
00:05:06,661 --> 00:05:09,262
But to offer presence.

77
00:05:09,262 --> 00:05:11,816
You might silently say:

78
00:05:20,816 --> 00:05:20,816
<break time="3s" />

79
00:05:20,816 --> 00:05:23,927
I hear that each of you is trying to
help.

80
00:05:23,927 --> 00:05:27,224
I do not need you to agree immediately.

81
00:05:27,224 --> 00:05:30,335
I want to understand what each of you
carries.

82
00:05:30,335 --> 00:05:32,796
Now ask the parts:

83
00:05:44,796 --> 00:05:44,796
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

84
00:05:44,796 --> 00:05:47,257
What do you need from Self right now?

85
00:05:59,257 --> 00:05:59,257
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

86
00:05:59,257 --> 00:06:00,790
Maybe they need patience.

87
00:06:00,790 --> 00:06:01,579
Reassurance.

88
00:06:01,579 --> 00:06:02,415
Protection.

89
00:06:02,415 --> 00:06:03,251
A plan.

90
00:06:03,251 --> 00:06:03,808
Rest.

91
00:06:03,808 --> 00:06:04,597
Clarity.

92
00:06:04,597 --> 00:06:05,340
Time.

93
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:06,687
Respect.

94
00:06:06,687 --> 00:06:09,288
Imagine offering what feels possible.

95
00:06:21,288 --> 00:06:21,288
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

96
00:06:21,288 --> 00:06:23,238
Only what feels honest.

97
00:06:23,238 --> 00:06:27,418
Now notice if any younger or more
vulnerable part is nearby.

98
00:06:27,418 --> 00:06:29,276
Do not force it to come forward.

99
00:06:29,276 --> 00:06:30,994
Just notice.

100
00:06:30,994 --> 00:06:35,174
If a vulnerable part is present, ask the
protectors:

101
00:06:35,174 --> 00:06:40,840
Would it be okay if I simply notice this
part, without overwhelming it?

102
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:52,840
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

103
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:55,023
Respect the answer.

104
00:06:55,023 --> 00:06:57,391
Now return to the whole council.

105
00:06:57,391 --> 00:06:58,506
Ask:

106
00:06:58,506 --> 00:07:02,778
What is one thing you want me to remember
after this practice?

107
00:07:14,778 --> 00:07:14,778
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

108
00:07:14,778 --> 00:07:18,958
Let each part offer a word, image,
feeling, or message.

109
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:21,048
Now thank the council.

110
00:07:21,048 --> 00:07:23,556
Thank the parts that spoke.

111
00:07:23,556 --> 00:07:26,342
Thank the parts that stayed hidden.

112
00:07:26,342 --> 00:07:28,478
Thank the protectors.

113
00:07:28,478 --> 00:07:30,707
Thank the vulnerable parts.

114
00:07:30,707 --> 00:07:34,190
Thank the system for allowing this much
contact.

115
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:38,091
Imagine closing the council respectfully.

116
00:07:50,091 --> 00:07:50,091
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

117
00:07:50,091 --> 00:07:52,831
Parts can return to their places.

118
00:07:52,831 --> 00:07:55,850
The room remains available for future
meetings.

119
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:57,893
Nothing has to be finished today.

120
00:07:57,893 --> 00:07:59,333
Now return to your body.

121
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,005
Feel your breath.

122
00:08:01,005 --> 00:08:02,120
Feel your hands.

123
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,699
Feel the surface under you.

124
00:08:03,699 --> 00:08:05,835
Notice the room.

125
00:08:14,835 --> 00:08:14,835
<break time="3s" />

126
00:08:14,835 --> 00:08:17,111
Notice the present moment.

127
00:08:17,111 --> 00:08:19,154
Take a slow breath in.

128
00:08:28,154 --> 00:08:28,154
<break time="3s" />

129
00:08:28,154 --> 00:08:30,244
And let it out.

130
00:08:30,244 --> 00:08:33,263
When you are ready, gently return.

131
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:38,614
You do not have to make every part agree
today. The council can remain open inside

132
00:08:38,614 --> 00:08:43,634
you — a place where each voice can be
heard, where protection can soften over

133
00:08:43,634 --> 00:08:48,588
time, and where Self can keep learning
how to lead with steadiness and care.

